RATE SCHEDULE FOR REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
Sayreville Power Generation LP ("Sayreville") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power") from the facility located in Sayreville, New Jersey (the "Sayreville Facility") to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Rate Schedule sets forth Sayreville's charges for the provision of Reactive Power to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission").
REACTIVE POWER REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Effective on the date authorized by the Commission, the revenue requirement shall be:
Generation Facility Monthly Revenue Requirement Annual Revenue Requirement Sayreville Facility $33,333.33 $400,000 Total Revenue Requirement $33,333.33 $400,000
LOST OPPORTUNITY COSTS:
Sayreville shall receive from PJM Lost Opportunity Costs associated with the Sayreville Facility as set forth in Sections 3.2.3 and 3.2.3B of Schedule I of the Amended and Restated Operating Agreement of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., as amended from time to time.
